    {
      "type": "conversation",
      "title": "Conversation Practice 1（会話）: At the Library",
      "context": "Looking for a book.",
      "lines": [
        {
          "spk": "A",
          "jp": "すみません。図書館は どこですか。",
          "en": "Excuse me. Where is the library?",
          "terms": [
            "v_toshokan"
          ]
        },
        {
          "spk": "B",
          "jp": "地図が ありますか。",
          "en": "Do you have a map?",
          "terms": [
            "v_chizu",
            "v_aru"
          ]
        },
        {
          "spk": "A",
          "jp": "いいえ、ありません。この 地名は 何と 読みますか。",
          "en": "No, I don't. How do you read this place name?",
          "terms": [
            "v_chimei",
            "k_nani",
            { "id": "v_yomu", "form": "polite_masu" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "spk": "B",
          "jp": "「ほんまち」です。私が 道を 説明します。",
          "en": "It is 'Honmachi'. I will explain the way.",
          "terms": [
            "k_watashi",
            "k_michi",
            { "id": "v_setsumei", "form": "polite_masu" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
